TY  - JOUR
TI  - Disequilibrium Econometrics in Simultaneous Equations Systems
AU  - Gourieroux, C.
AU  - Laffont, J. J.
AU  - Monfort, A.
AB  - [This paper considers the econometric problems raised by multi-market disequilibrium models. It uses a specification which is derived from general disequilibrium theory and, therefore, provides a first bridge between the economic theory approach and the econometric theory approach of disequilibrium. The model is piecewise linear; the problem of the existence of a reduced form, which is a crucial issue in nonlinear models, is solved. Limited information estimators as well as full information estimators are proposed; a simple numerical algorithm is given for the computation of a FIML estimator.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1980
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1912019
